Jeff Wicks, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Police divers are on Monday expected to continue the search for a 21-year-old man who is missing and presumed drowned in the sea off Hawston near Hermanus.NSRI spokesperson Craig Lambinon said that rescue volunteers had responded to a report of a drowning at 16:00 on Sunday. &nbsp;&ldquo;On arrival at the scene a search commenced for a local man who had reportedly been seen going underwater 300 meters from shore after being swept off rocks by waves and caught in rip currents,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;Despite an extensive search no sign of the man has been found and a Police Dive Unit have been alerted and will continue and ongoing search operation. Police have opened an investigation,&rdquo; he added.&nbsp;In another incident, NSRI volunteers also responded to reports of a drowning in Glentana.&nbsp;&ldquo;Prior to our arriving on the scene, we were informed that lifeguards and paramedics were attending to an 11-year-old female who had washed onto the beach after getting into difficulty in the surf.&rdquo;&ldquo;The child was resuscitated on the beach and transported to hospital in a serious but stable condition,&rdquo; Lambinon said.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.